The paper deals with power control in wireless data networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of game theory to model the behavior of users in the network suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The focus on energy efficiency and the investigation of the effects of interference on receiver performance suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and signal processing (cs.SI).
